{"id": 7482, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2018", "session": "18M", "subtopic": "5-1-measuring-energy-changes", "title": "18M.1.SL.TZ2.15", "topic_id": "5", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Two 100 cm<sup>3</sup> aqueous solutions, one containing 0.010 mol NaOH and the other 0.010 mol HCl, are at the same temperature.</p>\n<p>When the two solutions are mixed the temperature rises by <em>y °</em>C.</p>\n<p>Assume the density of the final solution is 1.00 g cm<sup>−3</sup>.</p>\n<p>Specific heat capacity of water = 4.18 J g<sup>−1</sup> K<sup>−1</sup></p>\n<p>What is the enthalpy change of neutralization in kJ mol<sup>−1</sup>?</p>\n<p>A.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{200 \\times 4.18 \\times y}}{{1000 \\times 0.020}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>200</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>4.18</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mi>y</mi>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1000</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>0.020</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{200 \\times 4.18 \\times y}}{{1000 \\times 0.010}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>200</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>4.18</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mi>y</mi>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1000</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>0.010</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{100 \\times 4.18 \\times y}}{{1000 \\times 0.010}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>100</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>4.18</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mi>y</mi>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1000</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>0.010</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{200 \\times 4.18 \\times (y + 273)}}{{1000 \\times 0.010}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>200</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>4.18</